---
const lastUpdated = "April 29, 2026";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <link rel="icon" href="/favicon.ico" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="Pozool privacy policy for users, customers, and visitors."
    />
    <title>Privacy Policy | Pozool</title>
    <style>
      :root {
        --background: oklch(99% 0.005 70);
        --foreground: oklch(18% 0.02 60);
        --card: oklch(100% 0 0);
        --primary: oklch(70% 0.19 45);
        --muted-foreground: oklch(50% 0.02 60);
        --border: oklch(92% 0.012 70);
        --surface-warm: oklch(97% 0.02 70);
      }

      * {
        box-sizing: border-box;
      }

      body {
        margin: 0;
        font-family: Inter, system-ui, sans-serif;
        background: var(--background);
        color: var(--foreground);
        line-height: 1.7;
      }

      a {
        color: inherit;
      }

      .container {
        width: min(100%, 56rem);
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 0 1.5rem;
      }

      header,
      footer {
        background: var(--surface-warm);
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
      }

      footer {
        border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-bottom: 0;
      }

      .nav,
      footer .container {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: space-between;
        gap: 1rem;
        min-height: 4rem;
      }

      .brand {
        display: inline-flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 0.625rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        text-decoration: none;
      }

      .brand img {
        width: 2.25rem;
        height: 2.25rem;
        border-radius: 0.625rem;
      }

      .nav-links {
        display: flex;
        gap: 1rem;
        color: var(--muted-foreground);
        font-size: 0.9rem;
      }

      main {
        padding: 5rem 0;
      }

      .panel {
        padding: clamp(1.5rem, 4vw, 3rem);
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 1.25rem;
        background: var(--card);
      }

      h1 {
        margin: 0;
        font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 4rem);
        line-height: 1;
        letter-spacing: -0.04em;
      }

      h2 {
        margin: 2.5rem 0 0.75rem;
        font-size: 1.25rem;
        line-height: 1.25;
      }

      p,
      li {
        color: var(--muted-foreground);
      }

      .updated {
        margin-top: 1rem;
        color: var(--primary);
        font-weight: 700;
      }

      ul {
        padding-left: 1.25rem;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <header>
      <div class="container nav">
        <a class="brand" href="/">
          <img src="/pozool-logo.png" alt="Pozool" />
          <span>Pozool</span>
        </a>
        <nav class="nav-links" aria-label="Legal navigation">
          <a href="/terms">Terms</a>
          <a href="/">Home</a>
        </nav>
      </div>
    </header>

    <main>
      <div class="container">
        <article class="panel">
          <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
          <p class="updated">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

          <p>
            This Privacy Policy explains how Pozool ("Pozool," "we," "us," or "our") collects, uses,
            shares, and protects information when you visit our website, contact us, or use our
            property management products and related services.
          </p>

          <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
          <p>We may collect the following categories of information:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Account and contact information, such as name, email address, company name, phone number, and login credentials.</li>
            <li>Property and operational information, such as listings, reservations, guest details, payment status, cleaning tasks, messages, reports, and team activity.</li>
            <li>Billing information, such as plan details, invoices, payment method tokens, and transaction records processed by payment providers.</li>
            <li>Technical information, such as IP address, device type, browser, pages viewed, logs, cookies, and approximate location.</li>
            <li>Communications you send to us, including support requests, demo requests, feedback, and emails.</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>2. How We Use Information</h2>
          <p>We use information to provide, maintain, secure, and improve Pozool, including to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Operate reservation, calendar, payment tracking, messaging, reporting, and operational workflows.</li>
            <li>Create and manage accounts, authenticate users, and provide support.</li>
            <li>Process payments, invoices, and account administration.</li>
            <li>Communicate about demos, product updates, security notices, and service-related matters.</li>
            <li>Monitor performance, prevent fraud, troubleshoot issues, and protect Pozool, customers, guests, and third parties.</li>
            <li>Comply with legal obligations and enforce our agreements.</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>3. Customer and Guest Data</h2>
          <p>
            Customers are responsible for having the legal right to provide property, reservation,
            guest, owner, employee, contractor, and payment-related information to Pozool. Customers
            are also responsible for providing any required notices and obtaining any required
            consents from guests, owners, staff, contractors, or other individuals whose information
            is entered into or connected with Pozool.
          </p>

          <h2>4. Third-Party Services</h2>
          <p>
            Pozool may connect with third-party services, such as booking channels, payment
            processors, email providers, hosting providers, analytics tools, and support tools.
            These services may process information under their own terms and privacy policies.
            Pozool is not responsible for the privacy practices, security, availability, or content
            of third-party services.
          </p>

          <h2>5. How We Share Information</h2>
          <p>We may share information:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>With service providers that help us operate Pozool, subject to appropriate confidentiality or processing obligations.</li>
            <li>With third-party integrations that a customer authorizes or connects.</li>
            <li>With a customer’s authorized users, team members, or account administrators.</li>
            <li>When required by law, legal process, security needs, or to protect rights, property, and safety.</li>
            <li>In connection with a business transaction, such as a merger, acquisition, financing, restructuring, or sale of assets.</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>6. Cookies and Analytics</h2>
          <p>
            We may use cookies and similar technologies to keep the website and product working,
            remember preferences, understand usage, and improve performance. You can control cookies
            through your browser settings, but disabling cookies may affect functionality.
          </p>

          <h2>7. Data Retention</h2>
          <p>
            We retain information for as long as needed to provide services, comply with legal and
            accounting obligations, resolve disputes, enforce agreements, maintain security, and
            support legitimate business needs. We may retain backup copies for a limited period.
          </p>

          <h2>8. Security</h2>
          <p>
            We use reasonable administrative, technical, and organizational safeguards designed to
            protect information. No system is perfectly secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute
            security. Customers are responsible for keeping their credentials confidential and
            managing user access appropriately.
          </p>

          <h2>9. Privacy Rights</h2>
          <p>
            Depending on your location, you may have rights to access, correct, delete, export, or
            object to certain processing of your personal information. To make a request, contact us
            at hello@pozool.com. We may need to verify your identity and may deny requests where
            permitted by law.
          </p>

          <h2>10. International Use</h2>
          <p>
            Pozool may process information in countries other than where you live or operate. By
            using Pozool, you understand that information may be transferred to and processed in
            locations with different data protection laws.
          </p>

          <h2>11. Children</h2>
          <p>
            Pozool is not intended for children under 13, and we do not knowingly collect personal
            information from children. If you believe a child has provided information to us, contact
            us so we can take appropriate action.
          </p>

          <h2>12. Changes</h2>
          <p>
            We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Updates are effective when posted
            unless a different date is stated. Continued use of Pozool after an update means the
            updated policy applies.
          </p>

          <h2>13. Contact</h2>
          <p>
            Questions or requests can be sent to hello@pozool.com.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </main>

    <footer>
      <div class="container">
        <span>© 2026 Pozool</span>
        <a href="/terms">Terms of Service</a>
      </div>
    </footer>
  </body>
</html>
